[[/tab]]

[[tab The Summary]]

The basic premise of this series is that it's a character-driven narrative about the Serpent's Hand, a radical paranormal liberation movement. The focus is on the people that are part of the movement, their motivations and their actions. The plan is for the story to weave its way through other canons and settings like a serpent, with a maximally inclusive approach to canon.

This is a more ruthless version of the [[[serpent-s-hand-hub | Serpent's Hand]]] than you see in most tales, but since anyone who describes themself as part of the Hand can be considered a member of it, I don't see this as contradicting those other works. While I leave it to the reader to decide whether my cast are heroes or villains, they certainly see themselves as righteous rebels, courageously opposing the unjust authorities that violently impose Normalcy upon the world, although most are also driven by more selfish motivations. I've deliberately taken inspiration from real-life revolutionary movements, both in the idealism of their goals and the brutal pragmatism of their methods.

While so far this series has only been written by [[*user Jerden]], other people are welcome to contribute. Feel free to use the characters I've written, as either a brief cameo or as the focus of the work! If it doesn't irreconcilably contradict stuff I've already written or intend to write in future, I'll consider it canon and add it to The Library - the timeline's loose for a reason. The series is also open to including any work that explores similar themes (The Serpent's Hand opposing the status quo), even if it uses a completely different cast of characters - one of the motivations behind this series was the feeling that the main thing the Serpent's Hand lacked was a recurring cast of characters. Feel free to contact [[*user Jerden]] if you have any questions, I have a lot of ideas that I haven't written down yet.

Also, if anyone does feel like creating artwork depicting any of the cast or scenes from the series, I will (with the artist's permission) put it up on the hub, either in The Cast section or in a separate tab of its own. 

With that said, I have no expectation anyone else will want to contribute - if this just ends up being me, I'll be happy just to tell the stories I want to tell.

The Anomalous is on the Rise!

You cannot hold back the Future forever...

[[/tab]]

[[/tabview]]

